org.digijava.module.aim.config

Class AMPActionServlet

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.servlet.GenericServlet
      • javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
        • org.apache.struts.action.ActionServlet
          • org.digijava.module.aim.config.AMPActionServlet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig

    public class AMPActionServlet
extends org.apache.struts.action.ActionServlet
    Overrides the default struts ActionServlet When a user initiates an edit session, the system keep tracks of the activity id that is being edited. Then if the user moves out of the edit screens without actually saving the edited data, the system should have to remove the activity id from the list of activities being edited. Essentially, the system locks any activity that is being edited by a particular user and if the user abandons his wish to save the edited values, the system has to unlock those activities.
